2781/9682409","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?replyto=3546725","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3546725#t3546725","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3546725#t3546725","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3546725#t3546725","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"werthead","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://werthead.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":3546725,"talkid":13854,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3546725#t3546725","upictitle":"werthead: Dornish Flag","article":"I'd agree with Gardner Dozois for short-form. Those annual anthologies have done wonders for the genre.<br /><br />For long-form, I think SIMON SPANTON of Gollancz is extremely deserving of recognition. His past accomplishments include discovering Richard Morgan and Scott Lynch, whilst this year he brought Patrick Rothfuss and Andrzej Sapkowski (way past time, in the latter case) to the UK. And he also handled editorial duties on the two clear front-runners (IMO ;-) ) for Best Novel, McDonald's BRASYL and Morgan's BLACK MAN (aka THIRTEEN).","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"9 years ago","ctime":"February 25 2008, 00:50:31 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://werthead.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"werthead","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"werthead","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://werthead.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"werthead","ctime_ts":1203900631,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/68019935/9988566","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?replyto=3548005","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3548005#t3548005","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3548005#t3548005","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3548005#t3548005","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"biguglymandoll","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://biguglymandoll.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":3548005,"talkid":13859,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/38501.html?thread=3548005#t3548005","upictitle":"biguglymandoll: dragon","article":"While I'm de-lurking to post:  Mr. Martin, first and foremost, THANK YOU for putting your opinions and these notes here!  It really is a thrill to have a glimpse of your side of the industry in general and the Hugos in particular.  (Not least because I agree with you on most points, Gardner Dozois as strong case in point!  ;-)<br /><br />Thanks again!","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"9 years ago","ctime":"February 25 2008, 01:27:59 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://biguglymandoll.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"biguglymandoll","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"biguglymandoll","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://biguglymandoll.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"biguglymandoll","ctime_ts":1203902879,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/27638673/96711